00046 /* Period parameters */  
00047 #define N 624
00048 #define M 397
00049 #define MATRIX_A 0x9908b0dfUL   /* constant vector a */
00050 #define UPPER_MASK 0x80000000UL /* most significant w-r bits */
00051 #define LOWER_MASK 0x7fffffffUL /* least significant r bits */
00052 
00053 #ifdef __cplusplus
00054 extern "C" {
00055 #endif
00056 
00057 static unsigned long mt[N]; /* the array for the state vector  */
00058 static int mti=N+1; /* mti==N+1 means mt[N] is not initialized */
00059 
00060 /* initializes mt[N] with a seed */
00061 void init_genrand(unsigned long s)
00062 {
00063     mt[0]= s & 0xffffffffUL;
00064     for (mti=1; mti<N; mti++) {
00065         mt[mti] = 
00066             (1812433253UL * (mt[mti-1] ^ (mt[mti-1] >> 30)) + mti); 
00067         /* See Knuth TAOCP Vol2. 3rd Ed. P.106 for multiplier. */
00068         /* In the previous versions, MSBs of the seed affect   */
00069         /* only MSBs of the array mt[].                        */
00070         /* 2002/01/09 modified by Makoto Matsumoto             */
00071         mt[mti] &= 0xffffffffUL;
00072         /* for >32 bit machines */
00073     }
00074 }
00075 
00076 /* initialize by an array with array-length */
00077 /* init_key is the array for initializing keys */
00078 /* key_length is its length */
00079 /* slight change for C++, 2004/2/26 */
00080 void init_by_array(unsigned long init_key[], int key_length)
00081 {
00082     int i, j, k;
00083     init_genrand(19650218UL);
00084     i=1; j=0;
00085     k = (N>key_length ? N : key_length);
00086     for (; k; k--) {
00087         mt[i] = (mt[i] ^ ((mt[i-1] ^ (mt[i-1] >> 30)) * 1664525UL))
00088           + init_key[j] + j; /* non linear */
00089         mt[i] &= 0xffffffffUL; /* for WORDSIZE > 32 machines */
00090         i++; j++;
00091         if (i>=N) { mt[0] = mt[N-1]; i=1; }
00092         if (j>=key_length) j=0;
00093     }
00094     for (k=N-1; k; k--) {
00095         mt[i] = (mt[i] ^ ((mt[i-1] ^ (mt[i-1] >> 30)) * 1566083941UL))
00096           - i; /* non linear */
00097         mt[i] &= 0xffffffffUL; /* for WORDSIZE > 32 machines */
00098         i++;
00099         if (i>=N) { mt[0] = mt[N-1]; i=1; }
00100     }
00101 
00102     mt[0] = 0x80000000UL; /* MSB is 1; assuring non-zero initial array */ 
00103 }

00105 /* generates a random number on [0,0xffffffff]-interval */
00106 unsigned long genrand_int32(void)
00107 {
00108     unsigned long y;
00109     static unsigned long mag01[2]={0x0UL, MATRIX_A};
00110     /* mag01[x] = x * MATRIX_A  for x=0,1 */
00111 
00112     if (mti >= N) { /* generate N words at one time */
00113         int kk;
00114 
00115         if (mti == N+1)   /* if init_genrand() has not been called, */
00116             init_genrand(5489UL); /* a default initial seed is used */
00117 
00118         for (kk=0;kk<N-M;kk++) {
00119             y = (mt[kk]&UPPER_MASK)|(mt[kk+1]&LOWER_MASK);
00120             mt[kk] = mt[kk+M] ^ (y >> 1) ^ mag01[y & 0x1UL];
00121         }
00122         for (;kk<N-1;kk++) {
00123             y = (mt[kk]&UPPER_MASK)|(mt[kk+1]&LOWER_MASK);
00124             mt[kk] = mt[kk+(M-N)] ^ (y >> 1) ^ mag01[y & 0x1UL];
00125         }
00126         y = (mt[N-1]&UPPER_MASK)|(mt[0]&LOWER_MASK);
00127         mt[N-1] = mt[M-1] ^ (y >> 1) ^ mag01[y & 0x1UL];
00128 
00129         mti = 0;
00130     }
00131   
00132     y = mt[mti++];
00133 
00134     /* Tempering */
00135     y ^= (y >> 11);
00136     y ^= (y << 7) & 0x9d2c5680UL;
00137     y ^= (y << 15) & 0xefc60000UL;
00138     y ^= (y >> 18);
00139 
00140     return y;
00141 }

00143 /* generates a random number on [0,0x7fffffff]-interval */
00144 long genrand_int31(void)
00145 {
00146     return (long)(genrand_int32()>>1);
00147 }
00148 
00149 /* generates a random number on [0,1]-real-interval */
00150 double genrand_real1(void)
00151 {
00152     return genrand_int32()*(1.0/4294967295.0); 
00153     /* divided by 2^32-1 */ 
00154 }
00155 
00156 /* generates a random number on [0,1)-real-interval */
00157 double genrand_real2(void)
00158 {
00159     return genrand_int32()*(1.0/4294967296.0); 
00160     /* divided by 2^32 */
00161 }
00162 
00163 /* generates a random number on (0,1)-real-interval */
00164 double genrand_real3(void)
00165 {
00166     return (((double)genrand_int32()) + 0.5)*(1.0/4294967296.0); 
00167     /* divided by 2^32 */
00168 }

00170 /* generates a random number on [0,1) with 53-bit resolution*/
00171 double genrand_res53(void) 
00172 { 
00173     unsigned long a=genrand_int32()>>5, b=genrand_int32()>>6; 
00174     return(a*67108864.0+b)*(1.0/9007199254740992.0); 
00175 }
